PEOPLE v. BAUMEISTER. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 11, 1909.) Proceeding by the People of the State of New York against John J. Baumeister.

With this case has been consolidated in this court cases bearing titles as follows: People v. John McManus; People v. Ellen E. Peek; Matter of Frederick Williams.

No opinions. Motions granted. Orders filed.
